title: For Sale:  Dvorak Air Recoil System
postcontent: I have some very good condition Air Recoil System (ARS) (small air tether) for AR-15,  AK-47, or GLOCK 17. These kits will create about 85% of live fire recoil for the long guns and deliver great performance using 12 gram CO2 cartridges with a beltpack or you can attach th small air line (about 1/8") to a 20 ounce paintball bottle and get thousands of rounds very inexpensively. These kits have an MSRP of $2,495.00 new so these are availabe at a significant savings.I only have a few of these left, so hurry if you want the best selection. These air recoil kits can be adapated for use on any modern firearms simulator, can be paired up inexpensive web cam ranges, and are also great for simply getting in a lot of trigger pulls to improve and control your trigger control. These kits also make it 100% for you to practice holster draws and cycling your weapon, something you can never do with live fire ammo.Any of thses kits can be easliy installed on your weapon, take a minute or less to install, and requires no permanent modification of your weapon. Drop in the kit, practice, and convert back to your regular firearm with ease. Some people will refer to these as drop in recoil kits, air recoil kits, or air recoil systems. Finally, please don't let the term "tether" worry you - these are nothing like the tether on the FATS systems - rather, it refers to a very small air line that goes into the magazine. You can still easily work with a holster or sling for motion practice and they will not restrict your movement in any way.

title: For Sale:  Taurus Model 62 LA .22LR Stainless Lever Action Rifle
postcontent: I have a used Taurus 62 LA  (Lever Action) stainless steel .22LR rifle for sale, in very good to excellent condition.  These rifles were in production for less than two years, before Taurus discontinued production of all of their rimfire rifles.  To my knowledge, these were the only .22 stainless steel lever action rifles ever manufactured, by anyone!  They are EXTREMELY hard to find!  (I could not find any for sale on Texas Gun Trader, Armslist, GunsAmerica, or Gun Broker)  It features a 23 inch long button-rifled barrel, a 15 rd capacity, and a Brazilian hardwood stock & forearm.  My research indicates that this design was actually a prototype that Winchester made (but never put into production), based on their very popular Model 62 pump action .22 "Gallery Gun".  The internal parts look the same, other than the lever instead of the pump mechanism.  LIke the 62, this rifle does "take down" into two halves for storage & cleaning, by unscrewing the saddle ring / screw.  This rifle does have a few minor scratches & marks on the receiver and stock, but it fires and functions perfectly, and is covered by the Taurus Lifetime Warranty.  As a bonus, I am including a Taurus brand Optics rail (a $35 value) that mounts in place of the rear sight in the dovetail, to allow the use of a EER scope or red dot sight for more accuracy.My price is $800, with a $850 trade value.  I may be interested in trading for a new model CZ 75B Omega or nickle plated or alloy frame Browning High Power 9mm pistols, or "tactical" (not hunting) rifles or shotguns, but would prefer to sell rather than trade, and will meet in N. Austin.  Shipping may be possible, at additional cost.  Thank you.
